axs[1].set_title("PACF", fontdict = {'fontsize': 16})

Unit Root and Stationarity Tests¶

In [9]:
# Here AIC is used to choose the number of lags
# To use SBC, pass autolag="BIC" into the test (the results are virtually the same)
# More on the parameters of the adfuller function: https://www.statsmodels.org/dev/generated/statsmodels.tsa.stattools.adfuller.html

# ADF test with no intercept, no trend
adfresult_n = adfuller(df["diff"].dropna(), regression="n")
print('ADF Statistic (no intercept, no trend): %f' % adfresult_n[0])
print('p-value: %f' % adfresult_n[1])
print('Critical Values:')
for key, value in adfresult_n[4].items():
    print('\t%s: %.3f' % (key, value))

# ADF test with intercept only
adfresult_c = adfuller(df["diff"].dropna(), regression="c")
print('\nADF Statistic (intercept only): %f' % adfresult_c[0])
print('p-value: %f' % adfresult_c[1])
print('Critical Values:')
for key, value in adfresult_c[4].items():
    print('\t%s: %.3f' % (key, value))

# ADF test with intercept and trend
adfresult_ct = adfuller(df["diff"].dropna(), regression="ct")
print('\nADF Statistic (intercept and trend): %f' % adfresult_ct[0])
print('p-value: %f' % adfresult_ct[1])
print('Critical Values:')
for key, value in adfresult_ct[4].items():
    print('\t%s: %.3f' % (key, value))

# ARIMA(4,0,0)

series = df[["diff"]].dropna() # Getting the target series
series.index = series.index.to_period('Q') # Setting quarterly frequency

ARIMA4_0_0 = ARIMA(series, order=(4,0,0), trend='c')
model_fit = ARIMA4_0_0.fit(method='innovations_mle')

# Summary of fit model
print(model_fit.summary())

# Line plot of residuals
residuals = pd.DataFrame(model_fit.resid)
residuals.plot(legend=None, figsize=(10,7.5))
plt.show()

# ACF and PACF of residuals
with plt.style.context('seaborn-whitegrid'):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(7.5,5), sharex='all',)
plot_pacf(model_fit.resid, lags=30, ax=axs[1], alpha=None, zero=False, title=None)
plot_acf(model_fit.resid, lags=30, ax=axs[0], alpha=None, zero=False, title=None)
for a in axs:
    a.set_ylim(-0.3, 0.3)
    a.set_xticks([0, 5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30])
    a.tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=12)
    a.grid(False)
    a.tick_params(axis='both', labelrotation = 90, colors="black")
    a.yaxis.label.set_color('black')
    # "Confidence intervals" computed as done in EViews
    a.axhline(y=-1.96/np.sqrt(len(model_fit.resid)),linestyle='--',color='black')
    a.axhline(y=1.96/np.sqrt(len(model_fit.resid)),linestyle='--',color='black')


axs[0].set_ylabel("PACF", fontdict = {'fontsize': 16})
axs[1].set_ylabel("ACF", fontdict = {'fontsize': 16})

smat_aic = np.empty((11,11))

# Grid search over forecast diagnostics
bias = np.empty((11,11))

rmse = np.empty((11,11))

for p in range(0, 11):
    for q in range(0, 11):
        print(f"{p}, {q}")
        model = ARIMA(s_train, order=(p,1,q), trend='t')
        try:
            model_fit = model.fit(method='innovations_mle', gls_kwargs={'max_iter':80})
            
            # Check Prob(Q) for up to 10 lags
            if not all(model_fit.test_serial_correlation('ljungbox', lags=30)[0][1] >= 0.1):
                smat_aic[p][q] = -999
                smat_bic[p][q] = -999
                bias[p][q] = -999
                mse[p][q] = -999
                rmse[p][q] = -999
                se[p][q] = -999
                mae[p][q] = -999
                mape[p][q] = -999
                continue
                
            smat_aic[p][q] = model_fit.aic
            smat_bic[p][q] = model_fit.bic    
            
            pred = model_fit.get_prediction(start=np.min(s_valid.index), end=np.max(s_valid.index), dynamic=True)
            pred_val = pd.DataFrame(pred.predicted_mean)
            # conf_int = pred.conf_int().rename(columns={"lower sea_level_rise_uhslcfd": "lower", "upper sea_level_rise_uhslcfd": "upper"})
            
            bias[p][q] = np.average(s_valid.iloc[:, 0] - pred_val.iloc[:, 0])
            mse[p][q] = mean_squared_error(s_valid, pred_val)
            rmse[p][q] = np.sqrt(mse[p][q])
            se[p][q] = np.sqrt(mse[p][q] - bias[p][q]**2)
            mae[p][q] = mean_absolute_error(s_valid, pred_val)
            mape[p][q] = mean_absolute_percentage_error(s_valid, pred_val)
            
            
            
        except Warning as w:
            print(str(w))
        
        except Exception as e:
            print(str(e))

# Forecasting on the test set
predt = res.get_prediction(start=np.min(s_test.index), end=np.max(s_test.index), dynamic=True)
pred_test = pd.DataFrame(predt.predicted_mean).rename(columns={"predicted_mean": "ARIMA(9,1,0)"})
conf_int = predt.conf_int().rename(columns={"lower Training": "lower", "upper Training": "upper"})

bias_t = np.average(s_test.iloc[:, 0] - pred_test.iloc[:, 0])
mse_t = mean_squared_error(s_test, pred_test)
rmse_t = np.sqrt(mse_t)
se_t = np.sqrt(mse_t - bias_t**2)
mae_t = mean_absolute_error(s_test, pred_test)
mape_t = mean_absolute_percentage_error(s_test, pred_test)

print(bias_t, mse_t, rmse_t, se_t, mae_t, mape_t*100, sep="\n")
